\begin_layout Subsection
Known Issues
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following issues (including bugs and missing features) are acknowledged.
 Some of them should be solved soon; others may take longer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Document structure is not preserved for certain document categories: for
 example in articles sections start with a 
\family typewriter
<h2>
\family default
 element (when they should translate to 
\family typewriter
<h1>
\family default
).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
On Mac OS X the output of a message with Unicode characters may cause an
 error.
 Workaround: run 
\family typewriter
elyxer.py
\family default
 with the 
\family typewriter
--quiet
\family default
 option.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Phonetic alphabet symbols are not supported -- if generated with LyX they
 appear with a weird command syntax: 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\textipa{[sample]}}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Standard
This happens only in the HTML file converted with eLyXer, not from within
 LyX.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Note Comment
status open

\begin_layout Standard
By the way, the previous note (and this one) should not appear on the HTML.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Vertical spacing is not preserved.
 (It is hard to do in CSS without significant mangling.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Multi-column layouts are lost.
 This one is almost impossible to get right in CSS, so there are no plans
 to even try.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
BibTeX support is primitive.
 (Bear in mind that the minimalistic approach using templates can be improved,
 but it will never be perfect.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
ERT (bare TeX code) is ignored.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Images are lost during conversion from within LyX.
 We are working with LyX developers to solve the issue.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The table of contents (and lists of objects) are lost in translation.
 Since eLyXer is currently a single-pass converter, it cannot know beforehand
 what the document will contain.
 A second processing pass might be added in the future to address this issue.
\end_layout

